Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa has intervened in the Cricket SA governance fiasco. He's banned the cricket governing body. That means it's no longer recognised, and will not get government funding. Mthethwa will publish this in the government gazette before informing the ICC of his decision. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former International Cricket Council President Ray Mali has weighed in on the Cricket South Africa leadership crisis Mali believes Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa's intervention isn't good for the game of cricket. READ: Mthethwa expected to intervene on CSA matter On Friday, Mthethwa intervened in the CSA governance saga by de-funding the organisation and derecognising it. The intervention comes after numerous attempts by the minister to allow CSA and its Members Council to agree on a new governance structure.